properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 9 at 3:20PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...FREEZING DRIZZLE OVER NORTHERN WISCONSIN THROUGH THIS
EVENING...
...HEAVY SNOW POSSIBLE NORTHEAST AND EAST CENTRAL WISCONSIN LATE
SATURDAY AFTERNOON AND SATURDAY NIGHT...

.Freezing drizzle will linger across northern Wisconsin this
evening, resulting in icy road conditions.

A strong low pressure system may bring a swath of heavy snow to
northeast and east central Wisconsin late Saturday afternoon and
Saturday night. Snowfall amounts of 6 to 12 inches are possible.
Strong north to northeast winds will result in blowing snow. There
will also be increased potential for ice shoves, lakeshore and
bayshore flooding, and shoreline erosion.

* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 12
inches possible. Winds could gust as high as 40 mph, causing
considerable blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central and northeast
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible. Areas of
blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong north to northeast winds will
increase the potential for ice shoves, lakeshore and bayshore
flooding, and shoreline erosion.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
